  <p>When I first heard this news I thought it may cause a few branding issues in the UK due to ITV being the name of a channel. Way ahead of me the lawyers for ITV seem to be investigating whether this is going to happen and whether they'll have a case to take Apple to court over it. I think there's a pretty good chance that if the name change does happen that ITV will be in with a strong case to protect it's name which may mean either a name change for the UK market or Apple having to license the name from them.&nbsp;</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/NewEarthOnline/NewsAndArticles/~4/nGGZoYxMfTE" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
